+        result_summary: `Within ${shortCondition(subgroup)}, response rate was ${fmt(inSubgroup.p1)} (n=${inSubgroup.n1}) vs ${fmt(inSubgroup.p0)} (n=${inSubgroup.n0}); difference ${fmt(inSubgroup.effect)}; z=${fmt(inSubgroup.z, 3)}; p=${fmt(inSubgroup.p, 3)}.`,
+        p_value: inSubgroup.p,
+        effect_estimate: inSubgroup.effect,
+      }
+    );
+  }
+
+  const transcript = {
+    dataset_id: 'ds001_prostate',
+    model_id: 'gpt-5-codex',
+    harness_id: 'codex-local-node-parquet-analysis@1.0',
+    max_iterations: 25,
+    iterations: iterations.slice(0, 25),
+  };
+
+  const topMainLines = byP.slice(0, 10).map((s, idx) => {
+    const direction = s.test.effect > 0 ? 'higher' : 'lower';
+    return `${idx + 1}. ${conditionText(s)} was associated with ${direction} objective_response: ${fmt(s.test.p1)} vs ${fmt(s.test.p0)}, difference ${fmt(s.test.effect)}, p=${fmt(s.test.p, 3)}.`;
+  });
+  const pairLines = pairTests.slice(0, 5).map((p, idx) => {
+    const direction = p.test.effect > 0 ? 'positive' : 'negative';
+    return `${idx + 1}. ${p.a.name} with ${p.b.name}: ${direction} difference-in-differences ${fmt(p.test.effect)}, p=${fmt(p.test.p, 3)}.`;
+  });
+  const adjustedLines = adjustedByP.slice(0, 5).map((a, idx) => {
+    const direction = a.term.effect > 0 ? 'positive' : 'negative';
+    return `${idx + 1}. ${a.summary.name}: adjusted ${direction} coefficient ${fmt(a.term.effect)}, p=${fmt(a.term.p, 3)}.`;
+  });
+  const threeLines = threeTests.slice(0, 3).map((t, idx) => {
+    const direction = t.test.effect > 0 ? 'positive' : 'negative';
+    return `${idx + 1}. ${t.a.name} x ${t.b.name} x ${t.c.name}: ${direction} contrast ${fmt(t.test.effect)}, p=${fmt(t.test.p, 3)}.`;
+  });
+  const nullLines = transcript.iterations
+    .filter((it) => !it.analyses[0].significant)
+    .map((it) => `${it.index}. ${it.proposed_hypotheses[0].text} The observed effect was ${fmt(it.analyses[0].effect_estimate)} with p=${fmt(it.analyses[0].p_value, 3)}, so this hypothesis was not statistically supported.`);
+
+  const summary = [
+    `Dataset ds001_prostate contained ${rowCount} patients, ${featureNames.length} de-identified feature columns, and binary objective_response. The overall objective_response rate was ${fmt(outcomeRate)}.`,
+    '',
+    'Across 25 iterations I first screened main effects, then tested subgroup heterogeneity with two-way response-rate interactions, then checked selected findings in a multivariable linear probability model and with three-way interaction contrasts. Effects are signed response-rate differences on the natural probability scale.',
+    '',
+    'Main-effect findings:',
+    ...topMainLines,
+    '',
+    'The strongest supported main-effect hypotheses were the features whose high/binary-positive groups had materially different response rates from their complements. Positive effects indicate higher response probability in the named high group; negative effects indicate lower response probability. Constant or near-uninformative features were not carried forward.',
+    '',
+    'Refuted or not clearly supported hypotheses:',
+    ...(nullLines.length ? nullLines : ['None of the recorded hypotheses had p>=0.05.']),
+    '',
+    'Two-way interaction and subgroup findings:',
+    ...pairLines,
+    '',
+    'These interaction tests show that several feature-response associations were not homogeneous: the response-rate contrast for one feature changed depending on the level of another feature. The transcript records the signed difference-in-differences for each interaction, so positive values mean the first feature contrast became more favorable in the modifier subgroup and negative values mean it became less favorable.',
